The two numbers from the image were the row/column points where words connected.

In total, there were 17 variations of the image. This was the start of the CyberBrokers Quest community, as people had to work together in Discord to collect all the pieces in order to solve the puzzle. 

The result of combining all of the pieces was a crossword puzzle. (4/7)

Like all of our puzzles, this was a community effort involving collaborative problem solving. 

At the bottom of each newsletter was an image that contained a word and two numbers. It wasn‚Äôt long before people realized they had different words/numbers in their newsletters. (3/7) https://t.co/U9ErYAtRR6

In January 2022, the second chapter of CyberBrokers lore was released via newsletter. In addition to learning more about Spice, Unironic Ken, and The Paradigm Lost, it contained the first ever CyberBrokers puzzle. (2/7)

Ken and Zinc set off across the city, following clues given by The Moderator. Eventually they discover that the Failsafe Alpha is being caused by ShaDAO, using a device stored in one of their warehouses. They infiltrate and destroy the device, but only Zinc manages to escape.

Zinc and Unironic Ken meet. There is tension and division between the two. Ken has received a message from Spice concerning Failsafe Alpha. Shortly afterwards, another message appears from someone calling themselves ‚ÄòThe Moderator‚Äô, offering help in getting Spice back into TPL.

Spice and her friend, Sybil, set off to check the solar collectors, but the strange timing of Failsafe Alpha feels suspicious to Spice. She instead sets off to find a P.O.S.T. box - an old analogue device that allows messages to be sent into the Paradigm from the real world.

Spice almost gets d-mezzed herself as she speeds across the city to find Zinc. She can‚Äôt find Ken since the three of them lost each other in the confusion. Before Spice and Zinc can come up with a plan, however, Spice is suddenly kicked out of TPL.

Team Soul ended up wracking up the most points, so Part 2 moved forward based on their team‚Äôs task to spread the message by protesting at the Merkle Tree, wrapping up Quest #2.

Team Soul had to work with Ken to drum up support for a protest at the Merkle Tree. They had to piece together a map in order to figure out how to avoid any Demons prowling the streets and figure out where fellow supportive brokers were located.

Team Body had to infiltrate a meeting for an unknown TV show at the PBC so they could cause a distraction and Zinc could sneak in to air the message. The team had to solve a logic puzzle with show names, time slots and channels to figure out the name of the show for the meeting.

Team Mind, on Spice‚Äôs orders, had to get an Incumbent on their side. They had to decode how to get in contact with one using the Incumbent's District number and a T9 conversion, a phone dial pad texting format.

Part 1 of Chapter 5 was already written in stone, but it was up to the CyberBrokers teams to determine how the story continued. Each team had different tasks to complete and were awarded points for completing them.

Spice was able to break into data center servers and give CyberBrokers access to the Power Eleven network. Brokers then were able to connect to the terminal and were broken up into teams based on their highest Mind, Body, or Soul stat.

But there was one last puzzle to solve. As each firewall fell, the DNA profile of a broker was revealed. After decoding how to unzip the DNA strands, Spice discovered that all broker DNA can be traced back to Asherah, leading her to the shocking truth that CyberBrokers are AI.

Spice then got into the mainframe for the last time on The Ethereal Node site. Cyberbrokers connected and received data based on the first letter of their names. After decoding a list of dance moves the password 'glitchin‚Äô moves' was produced and used to breach the last firewall.
The cipher revealed the password to bring down the fourth firewall: 'gunters paradise'.

Spice moved on to the Power Eleven site, where using the terminal she was able to give mainframe access to the brokers. Brokers had to use Soul scores to link the data output together using a circuit board cipher.

Spice then found the hidden mainframe page on the PandaPandaPanda site. Brokers connected to the mainframe and using all of the different Talents had to pair the data output to different constellations to get the password ‚Äòpasithee‚Äô to breach the third firewall.
The team was able to enter ‚Äòdichloromethane‚Äô, the password to bring down the second firewall.

Next Spice infiltrated the Polymeta site. CyberBrokers connected to the mainframe once again, this time using their Body scores to decode the received data. After pairing up the decoded words with elements, brokers used atomic weights to string together the pairs into words.

Spice was able to locate a hidden page on the VDreamscape website where CyberBrokers could connect to the mainframe. After decoding a series of GPS locations using the Mind score of all connected brokers, the password ‚Äòfallingwater‚Äô was used to breach the first firewall.
